urls.title: Changelog
urls.description: Added support for the convolution algorithm described by Hughes et al. (2023, DOI: 10.1007/s10980-023-01619-9): This algorithm is very memory efficient and fast, making it a good choice in memory-constrained scenarios. Not currently supported for all metrics. Only supported with metrics that use the init parameter. Long-term metrics have indeterminate run times that can be either really fast or really slow, depending on the data used to setup the model. Does not currently support NA values in landscape
